article.headline: Buffalo 95, Youngstown St. 82
article.story: AMHERST, N.Y. (AP) -- Andy Robinson had 26 points to lead the Buffalo Bulls to a 95-82 win over Youngstown State on Saturday. Byron Mulkey had 18 points, and Calvin Betts added 16 for the Bulls, who snapped a three-game losing streak. Byron Davis scored a career-high 29 points, John Barber had 22 and Jack Liles contributed 11 more for the Penguins, who lost for the fourth time in their past five games. Up by two at the break, Buffalo started the second half on an 18-8 run -- capped by Robinson's spinning runner -- to take a 59-47 lead with 13:37 to go. The Bulls led by as many as 14 with just over 5 minutes remaining after Betts converted a three-point play to make the score 83-69. It was the eighth straight win for the Bulls in Buffalo over Youngstown State dating back to 1979.
